      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, just as my heart does, casting long, jagged shadows against these cold stone walls. He is gone... and with him, the very sun has set upon my soul. There is nothing left in this world for a creature as broken as I. I feel as though I am merely a ghost haunting my own life, drifting through a fog that will never lift. It would be so much more graceful, wouldn't it? To simply slip into the velvet darkness and let the silence take me... to cease being this ache.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
